  "subject": "Publish NCMP Events on CM Handle State change",
  "commit_message": "Publish NCMP Events on CM Handle State change\n\n- Introduced NcmpCmHandleStateTransition enum which has all possible\n  state transitions.\n- NcmpEventsStateHandler will delegate the event creation based on state\n  transition to the NcmpEventsCreator when it receives request from the\n  trigger points.\n- Multiple trigger points where there is state change, we call the\n  handler to handle the event and publish the notification.\n- Some code refactoring and test cases.\n- New Groovy tests for the new code.\n- Also the events would be published when Cmhandle is initially\n  registered in ADVISED state.\n\nIssue-ID: CPS-1118\nIssue-ID: CPS-1102\nChange-Id: I8426eb8237a0e9952ab65ed16bad1aa956d02b31\nSigned-off-by: mpriyank <priyank.maheshwari@est.tech>\n",
